AB  - The European Commission promotes the Horizon 2020 Framework Programme for Research and Innovation since 1984. Horizon 2020 is open to everyone but the project coordinator should from EU countries. In 2016, a “Greening the Economy” call was announced. A proposal entitled “Regenarating ECOsystems with Nature-based solutions for hydro-meteorological risk rEduCTion (RECONECT)” was approved in November 2017 after one-year review processes. The National Cheng Kung University (NCKU) from Taiwan is one of the RECONECT 36 partners that from 18 countries. The Ministry of Science and Technology of Taiwan encourages and supports the Taiwanese research institutions to join the H2020 projects. This proposal is presented under this background. RECONECT aims to contribute to European reference framework on Nature Based Solutions (NBS) by demonstrating, referencing and upscaling large scale NBS and by stimulating a new culture for 'land use planning' that links the reduction of risks with local and regional development objectives in a sustainable way. To do that, RECONECT draws upon the network of carefully selected Demonstrators and Collaborators that cover a range of local conditions, geographic characteristics, governance structures and social/cultural settings to successfully upscale NBS throughout Europe and Internationally. NCKU plays as one of the International collaborators in RECONECT. Most of RECONECT partners focus on the application of NBS for inland problems such as flooding in the city or the landslide in the mountain. NCKU focuses on the application of NBS for coastal protection. Due to economy development request in the past 30 years, the coastal areas were heavy protected by hard constructions such as the grey sea dykes. It is less than 50% of the existing of nature coastline in Taiwan. Nowadays, people hope to enjoy the service of the sea but also hope they can be well protected when needed. NBS may be one of the approaches for Taiwan. This project proposes three strategies for NBS application in the coastal area. They are (1) remove (or partly remove) unnecessary artificial structures at the coastal area. (2) use nature material for coastal protection. (3) prepare room for the sea. Under the strategies, four research topics will be carried out in this project. They are (1) use of plants (such as Mangrove) to reduce ocean wave impact for the coastal area. (2) Reduce the height of sea dyke. (3) new coastal protection materials including oyster wave breaker and wooden groin. (4) Remove low-used fishing harbors to make more space for the sea. This study will develop models to assess the coastal protection capability and the eco-services, especially under the attacks of extreme weather conditions. This project works on coastal protection NBS and shares the experiences and outcomes with RECONECT partners. In the other hand, we learns from RECONECT partners to see NBS on inland problems application. It is necessary to attend the RECONECT meeting in Europe every 6 months. In addition, this project is going to arrange the 3 RECONECT Taiwan Workshops during the project periods to share with Taiwan local persons. This project will bring technical outcomes together with practical experiences.
